      <div class="container">
        <h2>‚ùì FAQs</h2>
        <div class="faq-container">
          <div class="faq-item">
            <h3>Do smartboards work with gloves?</h3>
            <p>
              It depends on the touch technology. Infrared (IR) and optical
              systems work with gloves, while capacitive screens typically don't
              unless they're specially designed for capacitive touch.
            </p>
          </div>
          <div class="faq-item">
            <h3>Which technology is best for artists?</h3>
            <p>
              Electromagnetic Resonance (EMR) technology paired with OLED
              displays offers the highest precision and pressure sensitivity,
              making it ideal for artists and designers who need detailed
              control.
            </p>
          </div>
          <div class="faq-item">
            <h3>What's the lifespan of a smartboard?</h3>
            <p>
              Most quality smart whiteboards have a lifespan of 5-7 years with
              regular use. OLED displays may have shorter lifespans (3-5 years)
              while LED displays can last 7-10 years with proper care.
            </p>
          </div>
          <div class="faq-item">
            <h3>Is a special pen always required?</h3>
            <p>
              No. IR, optical, and resistive technologies work with any object.
              EMR requires a special pen, while capacitive screens work with
              fingers and compatible styluses.
            </p>
          </div>
